*** Katta Dropbox Logger v0.3 ***


Usage:
  pydlog.py [-h] [--home HOME] [--logfile LOGFILE] [-d] [--logout]
		  [--background]

  Log to file Dropbox events

  optional arguments:
    -h, --help         show this help message and exit
    --home HOME        set the user home dir (default: '~')
    --logfile LOGFILE  set the log file (default: '~/Dropbox/dropbox.log')
    -d, --debug        run in debug mode (more verbose)
    --logout           logout account removing application file stored in home
		      directory
    --background       fork to background



 Example:

  python pydlog.py --logfile ~/dropbox.log --background
  
  
Dependecies:

 daemon: library to implement a well-behaved Unix daemon process ( http://pypi.python.org/pypi/python-daemon )